After this edifying address, he bade all in succession approach for his kiss. He received the sacrament of the communion; and altogether forbade that they should weep for him. Having stretched out his hand, and made the sign of the cross over his whole body, he commanded that they should sing a psahn. When the grief that overspread them kept them silent, he himself started the psahn‚ “ Praise ye the Lord in his sanctuary; let everything that hath breath praise the Lord.'' 2 And so, on the eighth of January, repeating this verse, while we could hardly make the responses‚ he fell asleep in the Lord.
